gs such as the Casa Rosada, the Cathedral and the City Hall. From here you will continue through the bohemian neighbourhood of San Telmo and on to the famous La Boca Juniors Football Stadium where there will be a stop and you can pay an optional visit inside if you wish.It is then time to make the short transfer to the colourful and iconic barrio of La Boca. This area retains a strong European flavour and you are likely to see Tango performances all around you as you stroll around. Next you will continue along the fashionable Avenida de Mayo and the dynamic Avenida Corrientes to the final stop and end of this trip which is Puerto Madero, a busy gastronomic and entertainment area with many restaurants and bars to choose from.</p><p>In the evening you will head out to watch Argentina's most famous dance, the passionate and dramatic Tango. Folklore has it that it began in the bordellos of long-ago Buenos Aires as men waiting for their 'ladies' passed time by dancing amongst themselves. Today, tango shows are supremely entertaining with their grand feats of athleticism and you will witness these as you enjoy dinner.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s), 1 Dinner(s)</meals></itinerary><itinerary><day1>9</day1><day2>9</day2><destfrom>Buenos Aires</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>Today is free to enjoy everything the city has to offer.</p><p>If you would a little time to relax, there are many green spaces such as Costanera Sur Ecological Reserve, an 865-acre swath of marshland along the R?o de la Plata.</p><p>There are also several optional excursions you could take. Just outside the city, the open grassland of Las Pampas is home to many working estancias where you could spend the day learning about the life of Argentinian cowboys - the Gauchos. The waterways of the Tigre Delta offers a peaceful boat ride where you can see local stilt houses and colonial mansions and you can 